[SN]TITLE[SN]
Driver found guilty of A952 Mintlaw death crash charge

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A motorist has been found guilty of causing the death of a man by driving carelessly on an Aberdeenshire road.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Driver Henry McPherson, 61, from St Fergus, died after the accident on the A952 near Mintlaw in 2014.
Pauline Flynn, 36, had denied causing death by careless driving by being on the wrong side of the road.
Flynn, of Mintlaw, was found guilty by a jury by a majority at Peterhead Sheriff Court. Sentence was deferred for background reports.
